Permission is granted to the project sponsor, authorized university personnel, and approved evaluators to review, demonstrate, and assess the Software for academic and project evaluation purposes only.

No part of the Software may be copied, modified, distributed, published, sublicensed, or used for commercial or public purposes without prior written permission from the project team and sponsor. Public release of the source code or system design is expressly prohibited.

This Software may reflect workflows and operational practices relevant to correctional and reentry services. As such, it should not be deployed, reused, or repurposed without proper review, authorization, and compliance with applicable organizational, legal, and security requirements.

All data used in demonstrations or testing must be synthetic or anonymized. The project team does not claim ownership of any real-world data belonging to the sponsor.
